1. Write on the terminal 

nano can_gui.py

2. Paste the code

Copy your full Python code and paste it into nano.

In Raspberry Pi terminal:

paste with right click
or
press Shift + Ctrl + V
4. Save the file

Press:
Ctrl + O → save
then press Enter
then Ctrl + X → exit

So the full order is:

Ctrl + O → Enter → Ctrl + X


5. Install required packages

sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y python3-pip python3-tk
pip3 install python-can --break-system-packages


6. Run the program

python3 can_gui.py

7. If the GUI does not open

It usually means:

tkinter is not installed
or you are using terminal without desktop session

Then check with:

echo $DISPLAY
